   <mods:abstract>Same as Na1I: 3517. Contains copy of letter from Evert Van Alen, 20 June
            1814, informing him of the sale of part of his land to pay taxes assessed for building a
            road from Albany to the River St. Lawrence. Ask his opinion in consequence of the letter
            to him from Evert Van Alen did not prevent the sale of the most valuable part of his
            property. Before he advances the money for redeeming the land, wishes to know John Jay's
            opinion as to the value of the property to an alien and non-resident. Is not disinclined
            to share in a tax for the improvement of the estate, but would like to know if it is
            actually being improved and whether if the property is ultimately sold it would be
            advantageous to now redeem the portion in question.</mods:abstract>
